narratives.question_text: Were the resources available to you - library, fabrication labs, classroom, software, desk space, etc. adequate for the fulfillment of the assigned work?  If not, please make suggestions.
comments: Everything was available. No improvement necessary.

The resources at Yale are amazing. My only complaint is about the Arts' Library book check-out policy, in addition to its hours. Architecture students work around the clock and 11 pm is a pretty early closing time. And one-day check-out is a bit stingy too, if it weren't for the student-shelf system it would be almost impossible to write a well-researched paper.
